  "conditionals": 51,
  "created": "2025-10-13",
  "description": "Mating type switching in budding yeast is a programmed gene conversion event controlled by the HO endonuclease, which initiates a DNA double-strand break at the MAT locus. The system demonstrates cell-type-specific and cell-cycle-regulated gene expression through multiple layers of control: SWI/SIN proteins activate HO transcription, mother-cell-specific expression through Ash1p repression in daughter cells, and tight G1-specific expression through Cln-CDK and SBF transcription factors. This represents one of nature's most sophisticated examples of coordinated gene regulation.",
  "id": "yeast_mating_type_switching",
  "keywords": [
    "mating type switching",
    "HO endonuclease",
    "gene conversion",
    "cell lineage",
    "chromatin remodeling",
    "SWI/SNF",
    "homologous recombination",
    "MAT locus",
    "HML",
    "HMR",
    "Ash1p",
    "SBF transcription",
    "mother-daughter asymmetry"
  ],
  "lastUpdated": "2025-10-13",
  "logicGates": {
    "and": 2,
    "not": 2,
    "or": 4
  },
  "mermaid": "graph TD\n    %% Cell Lineage Signal\n    A[Cell Division Event] --> B[Mother vs Daughter Fate]\n    B --> C{Mother Cell?}\n    \n    %% Mother Cell Path\n    C -->|Yes| D[No Ash1p in Nucleus]\n    D --> E[HO Promoter Accessible]\n    \n    %% Daughter Cell Path  \n    C -->|No| F[Ash1p Delivered to Daughter]\n    F --> G[Ash1p Nuclear Localization]\n    G --> H[Ash1p Binds HO URS1]\n    H --> I[\\HO Transcription Repressed/]\n    I --> J[No Mating Type Switch in Daughter]\n    \n    %% Cell Cycle Checkpoint\n    K[G1 Phase Entry] --> L[Cln3-Cdc28 Activity]\n    L --> M[SBF Activation]\n    M --> N[Swi4-Swi6 Complex]\n    N --> O{In G1 Phase?}\n    \n    %% Not G1 - No HO\n    O -->|No| P[\\HO URS2 Inactive/]\n    P --> Q[No HO Expression]\n    \n    %% G1 YES Path\n    O -->|Yes| R[SBF Binds HO URS2]\n    \n    %% AND Gate 1: Mother Cell AND G1\n    E --> ANDGATE1{Mother Cell AND<br/>G1 Phase?}\n    R --> ANDGATE1\n    ANDGATE1 -->|Yes| S[Chromatin Remodeling]\n    ANDGATE1 -->|No| Q\n    \n    %% SWI/SNF Complex Activation\n    S --> T[SWI/SNF Recruitment]\n    T --> U[Nucleosome Displacement]\n    U --> V[HO Promoter Opened]\n    V --> W[Swi5p Binds HO URS1]\n    W --> X[Basal Transcription Complex]\n    \n    %% AND Gate 2: Chromatin Open AND Swi5p\n    V --> ANDGATE2{Chromatin Open AND<br/>Swi5p Bound?}\n    W --> ANDGATE2\n    ANDGATE2 -->|Yes| Y[RNA Pol II Recruitment]\n    ANDGATE2 -->|No| Q\n    \n    %% HO Gene Expression\n    Y --> Z[HO mRNA Synthesis]\n    Z --> AA[HO mRNA Export]\n    AA --> AB[HO Translation]\n    AB --> AC[HO Endonuclease Protein]\n    \n    %% DNA Cleavage\n    AC --> AD[HO Nuclear Import]\n    AD --> AE[HO Recognizes MAT Locus]\n    AE --> AF[Double-Strand Break at MAT]\n    \n    %% Mating Type Information\n    AG[HML Silent Cassette] --> AH[MATa or MATalpha Info]\n    AI[/HMR Silent Cassette/] --> AJ[MATalpha or MATa Info]\n    \n    %% Gene Conversion Decision\n    AF --> AK{Current Mating<br/>Type?}\n    AK -->|MATa| AL[Copy from HMR]\n    AK -->|MATalpha| AM[Copy from HML]\n    \n    %% Homologous Recombination\n    AL --> AN[Rad51 Filament Formation]\n    AM --> AN\n    AJ --> AN\n    AH --> AN\n    AN --> AO[Homology Search]\n    AO --> AP[/Strand Invasion/]\n    AP --> AQ[DNA Synthesis]\n    AQ --> AR[Gene Conversion]\n    \n    %% Mating Type Change\n    AR --> AS[New MAT Allele]\n    AS --> AT[Mating Type Switch Complete]\n    AT --> AU{New Type?}\n    AU -->|Now a| AV[a-Cell Identity]\n    AU -->|Now alpha| AW[alpha-Cell Identity]\n    \n    %% Cellular Consequences\n    AV --> AX[a-Specific Gene Expression]\n    AW --> AY[alpha-Specific Gene Expression]\n    AX --> AZ[Can Mate with alpha]\n    AY --> BA[Can Mate with a]\n    AZ --> BB[Diploid Formation Competent]\n    BA --> BB\n    J --> BC[Maintains Daughter Identity]\n    Q --> BD[No Switch This Cycle]\n    \n    %% Styling\n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n    style A fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style B fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style C fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style D fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style E fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style F fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style G fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style H fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style I fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style J fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style K fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style L fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style M fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style N fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style O fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style P fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style Q fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style R fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style ANDGATE1 fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style S fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style T fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style U fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style V fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style W fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style X fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style ANDGATE2 fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style Y fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style Z fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AA fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AB fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AC fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AD fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AE fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AF fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AG fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AH fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AI fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AJ fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AK fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style AL fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AM fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AN fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AO fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AP fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AQ fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AR fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AS fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AT fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style AU fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style AV fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style AW fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style AX fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AY fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AZ fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BA fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BB fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BC fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BD fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000",
  "name": "Mating Type Switching and HO Endonuclease Control",
  "notGates": 2,
  "notes": "This flowchart represents mating type switching with 55 unique nodes (A-BD + ANDGATE1 + ANDGATE2). Contains 4 OR logic gates (mother vs daughter, G1 phase check, current mating type, new type) and 2 AND gates (mother AND G1, chromatin open AND Swi5p). Demonstrates sophisticated multi-level regulation combining cell lineage, cell cycle, and chromatin state. HO expression restricted to mother cells in G1 phase through independent regulatory pathways.",
  "organism": "S. cerevisiae",
  "relatedProcesses": [
    "yeast_gal_regulation",
    "yeast_cell_cycle_control"
  ],
  "scientificAccuracy": "This flowchart is based on verified genetic and molecular data from decades of research on yeast mating type switching. The HO gene regulation is one of the most well-characterized examples of combinatorial transcriptional control. All regulatory proteins, DNA binding sites, and cell-cycle dependencies have been validated against primary research sources.",
